{
  "texts": [
    "When well-resourced, these initiatives provide vital empirical findings revealing frontline policy implementation obstacles, while also supporting data assessments and enforcement actions under Article 40 [90,111].Equally important, sustained participant observation across product operations teams facilitates identifying crucial changes in governance processes made towards realigning company norms on transparency (Code: AT), risk analysis rigor and accountability towards regulatory aims amidst uncertainty.",
    "For instance, directly observing highrisk policy units over time would uncover ground realities, best practices and persistent friction points that shape how formal rules translate into practice (Code: NTD, RA), complementing external computational impact evaluations [125].Closely involved research gives essential methods for studying technology platforms [3,124].Discourse and Narrative Analysis Discourse analysis enables tracing subtle shifts in public narratives revealing underlying logics guiding platforms' cultural positions on emerging responsibilities, by combining computational techniques with critical reading (Code: AT) [71,83].",
    "For instance, analysis over time could determine evolving rhetoric usage in community standards (Code: NTD) and risk governance priorities (Code: RA) before/after DSA mechanisms enter force under transparency articles (Code: AT) and recurring assessments (Code: RA).",
    "For example, semantic analysis [71,83] and opinion detection [4] of community standards along with transparency reports [175] can surface evolving constructions of concepts like misinformation, platform responsibilities, and approaches to risk mitigation.",
    "Comparative approaches across firms also elucidate differences in translating common pressures, be that from broader public discourse expectations or specific regulatory provisions [3].Comparative Case Studies In-depth case examinations enable contrasting context-specific translations of formal DSA duties (Codes: NTD, AT, DD) into ground-level content moderation and risk governance practices by platforms across elections, health issues and geopolitical events (Code: RA) before/after adoption [5,44,149]."
  ]
}